2
00:02:54.923 --> 00:02:56.966
(SOBBING)

3
00:02:56.967 --> 00:03:01.967
(CONTINUES SPEAKING IN FOREIGN
LANGUAGE) (WOMEN WEEPING)

4
00:03:26.038 --> 00:03:29.332
He slaughtered our men...

5
00:03:29.333 --> 00:03:32.752
our brothers...

6
00:03:32.753 --> 00:03:33.961
OUT sons.

7
00:03:33.962 --> 00:03:36.422
(SCREAMING)

8
00:03:36.423 --> 00:03:40.718
The dead cry out
to us forjustice.

9
00:03:40.719 --> 00:03:44.930
On their souls. I swear to you.

10
00:03:44.931 --> 00:03:48.434
The man who took
our loved ones from us...

11
00:03:48.435 --> 00:03:53.435
the man who has brought us
such pain and sorrow.

12
00:03:54.024 --> 00:03:56.692
We Will find him.

13
00:03:56.693 --> 00:04:00.571
We will bring him here.

14
00:04:00.572 --> 00:04:05.572
We will not rest until his blood
flows into this very ground.

15
00:04:08.330 --> 00:04:13.330
We will have our revenge.

16
00:04:20.008 --> 00:04:25.008
(JAZZY MUSIC PLAYING)

17
00:04:32.604 --> 00:04:34.230
Sir? Excuse me.

18
00:04:34.231 --> 00:04:35.981
Yeah.

19
00:04:35.982 --> 00:04:38.526
The finish is included
in the cost of the wash.

20
00:04:38.527 --> 00:04:40.820
That's okay.
I'd rather do it myself.

21
00:04:40.821 --> 00:04:45.821
I'm a little obsessive that way.

22
00:05:24.990 --> 00:05:26.907
Lenore. Bryan.

23
00:05:26.908 --> 00:05:28.117
Hi. How are you?

24
00:05:28.118 --> 00:05:29.368
Fine. You?

25
00:05:29.369 --> 00:05:31.370
Mmm. good. good.

26
00:05:31.371 --> 00:05:32.371
Is something up?

27
00:05:32.372 --> 00:05:35.124
No. It's Saturday. two o'clock.

28
00:05:35.125 --> 00:05:37.168
Kim's driving lesson?

29
00:05:37.169 --> 00:05:39.003
Uh... Music lesson got switched.

30
00:05:39.004 --> 00:05:41.380
The Tuesday one
or the Friday one?

31
00:05:41.381 --> 00:05:43.382
I have no idea.

32
00:05:43.383 --> 00:05:44.758
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

33
00:05:44.759 --> 00:05:46.385
You know how kids are. Mmm-hmm.

34
00:05:46.386 --> 00:05:48.053
Especially the ones
who are desperate

35
00:05:48.054 --> 00:05:49.889
to pass their driving
test at the third try.

36
00:05:49.890 --> 00:05:51.056
She's not desperate.

37
00:05:51.057 --> 00:05:55.019
But she failed the test twice. Lennie.
It's important.

38
00:05:55.020 --> 00:05:59.648
So. where is she. really?

39
00:05:59.649 --> 00:06:01.525
I've never been
a good liar. have I?

40
00:06:01.526 --> 00:06:05.404
(CHUCKLING)
No. it's not yourforte.

41
00:06:05.405 --> 00:06:10.405
She's at her boyfriend.

42
00:06:11.286 --> 00:06:13.412
She has a boyfriend?

43
00:06:13.413 --> 00:06:15.998
Do you want to
come in for a drink?

44
00:06:15.999 --> 00:06:20.999
Yeah. I think you should.

45
00:06:21.213 --> 00:06:23.422
Why didn't she tell me. for God's sake?
(LENORE SIGHING)

46
00:06:23.423 --> 00:06:25.883
She probably didn't want you
running a full security check...

47
00:06:25.884 --> 00:06:30.884
of everything he's done
since kindergarten.

48
00:06:32.265 --> 00:06:34.350
But she's okay. right?

49
00:06:34.351 --> 00:06:39.351
Yeah. she's okay.

50
00:06:40.524 --> 00:06:44.527
Lennie. tell me
it's none of my business...

51
00:06:44.528 --> 00:06:47.363
but are you okay?

52
00:06:47.364 --> 00:06:48.656
(SIGHING)

53
00:06:48.657 --> 00:06:50.783
No.

54
00:06:50.784 --> 00:06:52.618
Not really.

55
00:06:52.619 --> 00:06:56.872
We've separated.

56
00:06:56.873 --> 00:07:01.043
Lennie. if there's
anything I can do...

57
00:07:01.044 --> 00:07:02.920
Well. I better...

58
00:07:02.921 --> 00:07:05.464
Thanks for the wine.

59
00:07:05.465 --> 00:07:07.174
Bryan.

60
00:07:07.175 --> 00:07:08.259
Don't.

61
00:07:08.260 --> 00:07:09.635
I don't even know
where the kid lives.

62
00:07:09.636 --> 00:07:14.181
You found her in a city of 12
million people within 72 hours.

63
00:07:14.182 --> 00:07:15.224
Promise me.

64
00:07:15.225 --> 00:07:17.726
I just told you... Promise.

65
00:07:17.727 --> 00:07:22.727
I'm going to give her her space.

66
00:07:25.318 --> 00:07:28.570
<i>Let me show you what I know</i>

67
00:07:28.571 --> 00:07:29.697
(PHONE BUZZING)

68
00:07:29.698 --> 00:07:34.285
<i>Let me take you where I'll go.</i>

69
00:07:34.286 --> 00:07:38.747
<i>I want to. yeah. share with you.</i>

70
00:07:38.748 --> 00:07:41.166
<i>Why won't you let me...</i>

71
00:07:41.167 --> 00:07:43.377
Um... Justwaitasec.

72
00:07:43.378 --> 00:07:43.878
What?

73
00:07:49.009 --> 00:07:52.011
I really like you.

74
00:07:52.012 --> 00:07:54.346
What is it?

75
00:07:54.347 --> 00:07:58.851
Um... It's okay. It's okay.

76
00:07:58.852 --> 00:08:03.852
Take all the time you need.

77
00:08:05.358 --> 00:08:10.358
(PHONE BUZZING)

78
00:08:15.785 --> 00:08:20.785
(RINGING DOORBELL)

79
00:08:23.043 --> 00:08:25.544
Hi.

80
00:08:25.545 --> 00:08:29.548
May I help you?

81
00:08:29.549 --> 00:08:31.550
Is Kim here?
Yeah. and you are...?

82
00:08:31.551 --> 00:08:33.218
Her father.

83
00:08:33.219 --> 00:08:37.514
Mr. Mills. what a pleasure.
I'm Jamie.

84
00:08:37.515 --> 00:08:41.477
Come in.

85
00:08:41.478 --> 00:08:43.187
Can I get you anything? A drink?

86
00:08:43.188 --> 00:08:46.023
Just my daughter will be fine.

87
00:08:46.024 --> 00:08:47.066
Dad?

88
00:08:47.067 --> 00:08:48.233
Hi.

89
00:08:48.234 --> 00:08:49.568
What are you doing here?

90
00:08:49.569 --> 00:08:52.404
I know how important it is
for you to pass your test.

91
00:08:52.405 --> 00:08:54.073
Wait. Kim. you don't
have a license?

92
00:08:54.074 --> 00:08:55.866
Have you ever tried to
parallel park an Escalade?

93
00:08:55.867 --> 00:08:58.410
I told you to take
the test with my car.

94
00:08:58.411 --> 00:08:59.023
God. Dad.

95
00:09:03.750 --> 00:09:06.210
Thank you.

96
00:09:06.211 --> 00:09:11.211
A pleasure to
meet you. Mr. Mills.

97
00:09:16.012 --> 00:09:19.098
BRYAN: <i>Could we slow down
a little bit. please?</i>

98
00:09:19.099 --> 00:09:21.600
I can't believe you just did that.
(SIGHING)

99
00:09:21.601 --> 00:09:23.435
You're leaving on
fall break next week.

100
00:09:23.436 --> 00:09:26.563
This is the only time I can get to
do this before I go to Istanbul.

101
00:09:26.564 --> 00:09:28.774
<i>We planned this. When you
make plans. you keep them.</i>

102
00:09:28.775 --> 00:09:31.402
No. Dad. you planned this.

103
00:09:31.403 --> 00:09:32.778
How did you even find me?

104
00:09:32.779 --> 00:09:33.904
Your mom and I were talking.

105
00:09:33.905 --> 00:09:35.406
Why didn't you tell me
you have a boyfriend?

106
00:09:35.407 --> 00:09:36.865
Because I knew
you'd overreact...

107
00:09:36.866 --> 00:09:40.577
and Ijustwant to feel normal
even if I'm just pretending.

108
00:09:40.578 --> 00:09:42.371
Remember to brake
before the stop...

109
00:09:42.372 --> 00:09:42.872
Dad.

110
00:09:47.794 --> 00:09:52.631
Mom doesn't know
where Jamie lives.

111
00:09:52.632 --> 00:09:53.757
(SIGHING)

112
00:09:53.758 --> 00:09:55.259
GPS?

113
00:09:55.260 --> 00:09:58.637
I had it installed in your phone.
I'm sorry.

114
00:09:58.638 --> 00:10:01.974
You hear so many scary stories of
goings-on with people your age...

115
00:10:01.975 --> 00:10:04.309
Dad. I don't even know how to
start feeling normal again...

116
00:10:04.310 --> 00:10:07.938
but this definitely isn't it.

117
00:10:07.939 --> 00:10:12.939
Kim. you can move.

118
00:10:22.620 --> 00:10:27.620
Use your side mirror.

119
00:10:37.177 --> 00:10:41.180
Perfect. Why couldn't you
do that in the test?

120
00:10:41.181 --> 00:10:42.514
I don't know.

121
00:10:42.515 --> 00:10:45.184
Maybe I didn't really
want a license.

122
00:10:45.185 --> 00:10:46.351
Listen...

123
00:10:46.352 --> 00:10:49.146
of course I know
where you're coming from.

124
00:10:49.147 --> 00:10:52.649
But you have to trust me
to figure this out.

125
00:10:52.650 --> 00:10:55.194
Don't do this again. please?

126
00:10:55.195 --> 00:10:57.029
I won't.

127
00:10:57.030 --> 00:11:00.282
And don't go running a background
check on him with your friends.

128
00:11:00.283 --> 00:11:03.452
I won't.

129
00:11:03.453 --> 00:11:04.453
<i>Okay-</i>

130
00:11:04.454 --> 00:11:06.455
See you Wednesday.

131
00:11:06.456 --> 00:11:08.790
Two o'clock.

132
00:11:08.791 --> 00:11:09.833
Love you.

133
00:11:09.834 --> 00:11:14.834
Hey. I love you.

134
00:11:36.736 --> 00:11:39.238
(PHONE RINGING)

135
00:11:39.239 --> 00:11:40.322
Yeah.

136
00:11:40.323 --> 00:11:42.699
Sam. Hi. It's me.

137
00:11:42.700 --> 00:11:46.495
Listen. I want you to run a check
on someone. Jamie Conrad.

138
00:11:46.496 --> 00:11:48.288
The usual. Not too deep.

139
00:11:48.289 --> 00:11:49.498
You got it.

140
00:11:49.499 --> 00:11:54.499
<i>Okay. Thanks.</i>

141
00:12:04.722 --> 00:12:06.098
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

142
00:12:06.099 --> 00:12:06.890
Sir.

143
00:12:06.891 --> 00:12:11.891
Thank you.

144
00:12:13.982 --> 00:12:15.816
Mr. Pitrel?

145
00:12:15.817 --> 00:12:18.110
I have a registered letter for you.

146
00:12:18.111 --> 00:12:23.111
- Can you take that up. Sébastien?
- Yes. sir.

147
00:12:24.075 --> 00:12:24.575
Here.

148
00:12:28.746 --> 00:12:29.358
Sébasüen?

149
00:12:45.888 --> 00:12:47.514
(GROANING)

150
00:12:47.515 --> 00:12:52.515
(SPITTING)

151
00:12:54.522 --> 00:12:55.981
Where is he?

152
00:12:55.982 --> 00:12:59.151
I told you.

153
00:12:59.152 --> 00:13:04.152
I don't know.

154
00:13:14.959 --> 00:13:19.546
Where is he?

155
00:13:19.547 --> 00:13:24.547
Where is he?

156
00:13:25.428 --> 00:13:25.928
<i>Okay-</i>

157
00:13:29.599 --> 00:13:31.516
(PANTING)

158
00:13:31.517 --> 00:13:33.352
You want to play with me.

159
00:13:33.353 --> 00:13:35.562
No. no!

160
00:13:35.563 --> 00:13:40.563
(CRYING OUT IN PAIN)

161
00:13:40.985 --> 00:13:43.779
But I'm a good player. too.

162
00:13:43.780 --> 00:13:48.780
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

163
00:13:50.453 --> 00:13:50.953
Shh!

164
00:13:56.084 --> 00:13:57.250
Look.

165
00:13:57.251 --> 00:14:00.212
PITREL: No. no!

166
00:14:00.213 --> 00:14:05.213
I guess the rules are changing.

167
00:14:06.719 --> 00:14:09.429
This man came to Paris.

168
00:14:09.430 --> 00:14:13.809
He used a card
to come into our house

169
00:14:13.810 --> 00:14:16.311
and kill my friends..

170
00:14:16.312 --> 00:14:21.312
And my brother.

171
00:14:23.403 --> 00:14:28.403
This is your card.

172
00:14:32.912 --> 00:14:35.664
Where is he?

173
00:14:35.665 --> 00:14:40.665
Where is he? (MUFFLED SCREAM)

174
00:14:43.089 --> 00:14:47.050
LENORE: Stu. where are you going?
Come back!

175
00:14:47.051 --> 00:14:52.051
(CAR ENGINE REVVING)

176
00:15:21.294 --> 00:15:23.211
What's happened? Are you okay?

177
00:15:23.212 --> 00:15:25.130
Yeah. I'm great.

178
00:15:25.131 --> 00:15:26.715
Come in. I'll get Kim.

179
00:15:26.716 --> 00:15:29.134
Hey. hey. hey-

180
00:15:29.135 --> 00:15:30.844
Lennie. talk to me.

181
00:15:30.845 --> 00:15:32.095
(SNIFFLING)

182
00:15:32.096 --> 00:15:36.141
We had this trip planned to
China for Kim's spring break...

183
00:15:36.142 --> 00:15:39.311
as a family. to try
and work things out.

184
00:15:39.312 --> 00:15:40.979
And when Stu and I...

185
00:15:40.980 --> 00:15:43.273
I just thought it would
be nice for Kim and I

186
00:15:43.274 --> 00:15:45.233
to be away together...

187
00:15:45.234 --> 00:15:47.277
away from all the tension.

188
00:15:47.278 --> 00:15:48.987
He canceled everything.

189
00:15:48.988 --> 00:15:50.739
All the reservations.

190
00:15:50.740 --> 00:15:55.740
I just can't believe
he did this to us.

191
00:15:57.288 --> 00:15:58.997
I'm just so tired.

192
00:15:58.998 --> 00:16:01.166
Just the fighting. the lawyers.

193
00:16:01.167 --> 00:16:03.084
He's turned into such a bastard.

194
00:16:03.085 --> 00:16:04.795
I'm sorry. Lennie.

195
00:16:04.796 --> 00:16:07.672
I'm sorry.

196
00:16:07.673 --> 00:16:10.509
I'm sorry. This is
really not your problem.

197
00:16:10.510 --> 00:16:14.012
It's my turn to have...

198
00:16:14.013 --> 00:16:15.472
I'll figure it out.

199
00:16:15.473 --> 00:16:17.098
Look_.

200
00:16:17.099 --> 00:16:19.851
Why don't you and
Kim come with me?

201
00:16:19.852 --> 00:16:22.854
But we can't impose on you.
You're working.

202
00:16:22.855 --> 00:16:24.189
You're not imposing.

203
00:16:24.190 --> 00:16:25.857
I'm working for three days.

204
00:16:25.858 --> 00:16:28.276
Then you can come over.

205
00:16:28.277 --> 00:16:29.694
It could be fun.

206
00:16:29.695 --> 00:16:31.863
That's so sweet.

207
00:16:31.864 --> 00:16:34.115
I don't know.
I can't think right now.

208
00:16:34.116 --> 00:16:36.827
Sure. I understand. No pressure.

209
00:16:36.828 --> 00:16:40.038
I leave in the morning.
Iwork three days. Call me.

210
00:16:40.039 --> 00:16:42.541
If you're coming. I'll hang around.
If not. I'll come back.

211
00:16:42.542 --> 00:16:43.708
That's it.

212
00:16:43.709 --> 00:16:45.335
I'll go get Kim.

213
00:16:45.336 --> 00:16:46.378
<i>Okay-</i>

214
00:16:46.379 --> 00:16:51.379
Thank you. Bryan.

215
00:16:53.886 --> 00:16:58.723
(SIGHING)

216
00:16:58.724 --> 00:17:00.308
<i>SAM: She is definitely coming.</i>

217
00:17:00.309 --> 00:17:02.644
I don't know. Sam. I don't know.
Oh. come on.

218
00:17:02.645 --> 00:17:04.896
You should have insisted.
Mmm-hmm.

219
00:17:04.897 --> 00:17:06.565
Come on. guys.
Cut me some slack.

220
00:17:06.566 --> 00:17:07.899
She's going through a hard time.

221
00:17:07.900 --> 00:17:09.359
I didn't want to
make it harder on her.

222
00:17:09.360 --> 00:17:11.069
She was confiding in me.

223
00:17:11.070 --> 00:17:13.864
Oh! I didn't know you guys
were still so cozy...

224
00:17:13.865 --> 00:17:16.199
that she shares her
marriage issues with you.

225
00:17:16.200 --> 00:17:17.576
Wait a minute.

226
00:17:17.577 --> 00:17:21.162
I know you guys were close.
obviously. but are you close again?

227
00:17:21.163 --> 00:17:22.581
Close like...

228
00:17:22.582 --> 00:17:24.249
I'll lay money she's still
got something for him.

229
00:17:24.250 --> 00:17:25.917
Don't go there. friend.

230
00:17:25.918 --> 00:17:28.670
(CHUCKLING) Maybe he still
has something for her!

231
00:17:28.671 --> 00:17:31.381
Can we talk about basketball?
For God's sake. come on!

232
00:17:31.382 --> 00:17:36.382
(LAUGHING)

233
00:17:48.274 --> 00:17:48.886
Istanbul.

234
00:17:59.368 --> 00:18:00.952
Thank you. Mr. Mills.

235
00:18:00.953 --> 00:18:05.953
You made my stay
feel very secure.

236
00:18:07.251 --> 00:18:09.711
Thank you.
Have a safe trip home.

237
00:18:09.712 --> 00:18:10.324
You also.

238
00:18:15.968 --> 00:18:20.968
(CHUCKUNG)

239
00:18:26.729 --> 00:18:29.564
<i>You've reached Lenore. Leave
a message after the beep.</i>

240
00:18:29.565 --> 00:18:31.441
Hey. it's me.

241
00:18:31.442 --> 00:18:32.984
No message from you...

242
00:18:32.985 --> 00:18:35.654
so I guess you probably
found some place to go.

243
00:18:35.655 --> 00:18:37.989
I hope things are
a little easier.

244
00:18:37.990 --> 00:18:41.284
If you ever need to talk
or anything. I'm here.

245
00:18:41.285 --> 00:18:42.911
I mean. I'll be there.

246
00:18:42.912 --> 00:18:45.914
I'll probably ship out tomorrow.

247
00:18:45.915 --> 00:18:48.166
No news from Kim.

248
00:18:48.167 --> 00:18:50.418
I guess she's busy with
the boyfriend and all.

249
00:18:50.419 --> 00:18:52.462
Dad.

250
00:18:52.463 --> 00:18:53.630
(CHUCKUNG)

251
00:18:53.631 --> 00:18:54.798
Surprise!

252
00:18:54.799 --> 00:18:57.842
Oh. my God. Kim. baby.

253
00:18:57.843 --> 00:19:00.011
Hey. Lennie. Hello. Bryan.

254
00:19:00.012 --> 00:19:02.847
I was just leaving you a message.
When I didn't hear. itwas...

255
00:19:02.848 --> 00:19:04.182
We wanted to surprise you.

256
00:19:04.183 --> 00:19:05.850
Well. you succeeded.

257
00:19:05.851 --> 00:19:07.018
(ALL CHUCKLING)

258
00:19:07.019 --> 00:19:08.436
You guys could have
been surprised.

259
00:19:08.437 --> 00:19:09.938
I could have been out
of here and headed home.

260
00:19:09.939 --> 00:19:11.523
Mom's been calling Sam.

261
00:19:11.524 --> 00:19:13.191
Oh. yeah? Uh-huh. Yes.

262
00:19:13.192 --> 00:19:14.651
We've been tracking you.

263
00:19:14.652 --> 00:19:16.861
Exactly. You're not the
only one Who's got moves.

264
00:19:16.862 --> 00:19:18.863
Apparently not.

265
00:19:18.864 --> 00:19:23.864
Welcome to Istanbul.

266
00:19:27.790 --> 00:19:29.582
Not too shabby. huh?

267
00:19:29.583 --> 00:19:31.042
Wow.

268
00:19:31.043 --> 00:19:33.545
Oh. my God.

269
00:19:33.546 --> 00:19:36.464
Mom. look at this.

270
00:19:36.465 --> 00:19:37.757
Oh. my God!

271
00:19:37.758 --> 00:19:38.925
KIM: It's crazy. right?

272
00:19:38.926 --> 00:19:40.260
LENORE: It's beautiful!

273
00:19:40.261 --> 00:19:42.387
Thank you so much. My pleasure.

274
00:19:42.388 --> 00:19:43.888
Listen. I'll let you
get settled...

275
00:19:43.889 --> 00:19:46.266
and I'll come and collect
you in half an hour?

276
00:19:46.267 --> 00:19:49.102
<i>Okay-</i>

277
00:19:49.103 --> 00:19:49.603
Later.

278
00:20:09.165 --> 00:20:14.165
Good morning.

279
00:20:16.422 --> 00:20:17.839
Good.

280
00:20:17.840 --> 00:20:18.757
Go.

281
00:20:18.758 --> 00:20:19.758
Fast.

282
00:20:19.759 --> 00:20:20.371
Let's go.

283
00:20:41.989 --> 00:20:46.989
(NEWS PLAYING ON TV)

284
00:21:07.765 --> 00:21:09.182
(DOORBELL RINGING)

285
00:21:09.183 --> 00:21:10.391
LENORE: Hey. Hey.

286
00:21:10.392 --> 00:21:11.976
You look great.

287
00:21:11.977 --> 00:21:13.686
You. too.

288
00:21:13.687 --> 00:21:16.147
So. where are we heading?

289
00:21:16.148 --> 00:21:19.984
Well. I am going nowhere.
I'm beat.

290
00:21:19.985 --> 00:21:23.530
I'm just going to take a nice
long bath and get into bed.

291
00:21:23.531 --> 00:21:24.656
Lennie. Are you sure?

292
00:21:24.657 --> 00:21:27.200
Yeah.

293
00:21:27.201 --> 00:21:29.160
I guess it's just
you and me. kiddo.

294
00:21:29.161 --> 00:21:32.831
Anything special
you'd like to do?

295
00:21:32.832 --> 00:21:37.335
Kind of. Maybe.

296
00:21:37.336 --> 00:21:42.336
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

297
00:22:01.610 --> 00:22:04.028
HGY' Hey-

298
00:22:04.029 --> 00:22:05.113
You ready to take off. too?

299
00:22:05.114 --> 00:22:07.156
No. I thought I'd stick around
for a couple of more hours.

300
00:22:07.157 --> 00:22:08.491
Really? Yeah.

301
00:22:08.492 --> 00:22:10.702
Cool. No. Just kidding.

302
00:22:10.703 --> 00:22:15.623
Come on. Let's go. All right.
It's so crazy here.

303
00:22:15.624 --> 00:22:20.624
On this side is Europe.
and the other side is Asia.

304
00:22:22.882 --> 00:22:26.634
And every conquest since.
for the last 2.500 years...

305
00:22:26.635 --> 00:22:30.054
whether it was the West going
East or the East going West...

306
00:22:30.055 --> 00:22:32.557
they all used this
very same waterway.

307
00:22:32.558 --> 00:22:33.892
(MAN SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

308
00:22:33.893 --> 00:22:35.935
You want some tea. baby? Yeah.

309
00:22:35.936 --> 00:22:37.562
Just one. please.

310
00:22:37.563 --> 00:22:39.939
How do you know all this stuff?

311
00:22:39.940 --> 00:22:41.566
How do I know it?

312
00:22:41.567 --> 00:22:45.904
I read it in a book
on the flight over.

313
00:22:45.905 --> 00:22:48.406
And you can borrow
it if you wish.

314
00:22:48.407 --> 00:22:50.742
Yeah. I would.

315
00:22:50.743 --> 00:22:54.245
So. this Jamie...

316
00:22:54.246 --> 00:22:57.290
Is it... serious?

317
00:22:57.291 --> 00:23:00.001
That was a really
smooth transition.

318
00:23:00.002 --> 00:23:02.003
(CHUCKUNG)

319
00:23:02.004 --> 00:23:03.421
I don't know.

320
00:23:03.422 --> 00:23:05.256
It's only been a few months.

321
00:23:05.257 --> 00:23:08.968
Are you in love with him?

322
00:23:08.969 --> 00:23:10.929
I guess I'm not sure yet.

323
00:23:10.930 --> 00:23:15.930
Have you ever
been in love before?

324
00:23:16.977 --> 00:23:19.979
Not the way that
Mom talks about it.

325
00:23:19.980 --> 00:23:22.148
How does she describe it?

326
00:23:22.149 --> 00:23:27.149
She said when you guys met...

327
00:23:27.363 --> 00:23:29.364
that it was super special.

328
00:23:29.365 --> 00:23:31.324
Super special? She said that?

329
00:23:31.325 --> 00:23:34.994
I think the exact
word she used was...

330
00:23:34.995 --> 00:23:39.123
"magical."

331
00:23:39.124 --> 00:23:41.292
Magical. huh?

332
00:23:41.293 --> 00:23:46.293
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

333
00:23:52.012 --> 00:23:57.012
(MUEZZIN CALL TO PRAYER)

334
00:24:25.504 --> 00:24:27.839
(GREETING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

335
00:24:27.840 --> 00:24:31.092
It's good to see
you again. my friend.

336
00:24:31.093 --> 00:24:32.885
(GREETING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

337
00:24:32.886 --> 00:24:34.971
Is everything prepared?

338
00:24:34.972 --> 00:24:37.306
As you requested.

339
00:24:37.307 --> 00:24:42.307
Ah! Perfect.

340
00:25:18.098 --> 00:25:21.392
(PHONE RINGING)

341
00:25:21.393 --> 00:25:23.519
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

342
00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:25.396
Yeah? He's in the lobby.

343
00:25:25.397 --> 00:25:27.148
Wait until he's outside.

344
00:25:27.149 --> 00:25:31.319
And remember. alive.

345
00:25:31.320 --> 00:25:36.320
He's on to me. I'm leaving.

346
00:25:50.756 --> 00:25:51.881
Hey. BRYAN: Hi.

347
00:25:51.882 --> 00:25:53.841
I thought we were
having lunch in the bazaar.

348
00:25:53.842 --> 00:25:55.009
Um...

349
00:25:55.010 --> 00:25:56.427
Jet lag just hit me...

350
00:25:56.428 --> 00:25:59.680
so I figured I'd veg out by
the pool and let you guys go.

351
00:25:59.681 --> 00:26:01.599
Meet up with you later?

352
00:26:01.600 --> 00:26:03.017
I guess. Okay with you?

353
00:26:03.018 --> 00:26:04.268
Of course. It's fine.

354
00:26:04.269 --> 00:26:06.229
Oh. okay. Bye. Hey. Kim.

355
00:26:06.230 --> 00:26:09.190
That book I was telling you about?
It's on my dresser.

356
00:26:09.191 --> 00:26:10.191
Definitely.

357
00:26:10.192 --> 00:26:12.193
No adventuring.
I'll go call the car.

358
00:26:12.194 --> 00:26:14.028
Have fun.

359
00:26:14.029 --> 00:26:15.780
Hey. Kim.

360
00:26:15.781 --> 00:26:17.281
(SOFTLY) I know
what you're doing.

361
00:26:17.282 --> 00:26:22.282
(CHUCKLING) What?

362
00:26:23.122 --> 00:26:25.581
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

363
00:26:25.582 --> 00:26:27.125
Yeah?

364
00:26:27.126 --> 00:26:29.919
The daughter is staying here.
What can we do?

365
00:26:29.920 --> 00:26:33.464
I want all three of them.

366
00:26:33.465 --> 00:26:37.218
Yes?

367
00:26:37.219 --> 00:26:40.471
She thinks we just
fell off the turnip truck.

368
00:26:40.472 --> 00:26:41.597
What do you mean?

369
00:26:41.598 --> 00:26:43.391
She's trying to play cupid.

370
00:26:43.392 --> 00:26:44.976
Oh. I see.

371
00:26:44.977 --> 00:26:46.477
When you first came back...

372
00:26:46.478 --> 00:26:48.229
and said you wanted to
make up for all that time

373
00:26:48.230 --> 00:26:50.148
that you lost with Kim? Uh-huh?

374
00:26:50.149 --> 00:26:52.942
I thought. "Right
Three weeks. he's gone."

375
00:26:52.943 --> 00:26:55.653
That was usually about the
limit you stuck around.

376
00:26:55.654 --> 00:27:00.241
Give or take a week.

377
00:27:00.242 --> 00:27:01.784
Not too close.

378
00:27:01.785 --> 00:27:04.996
LENORE: You really proved me wrong.
I thought you'd never change.

379
00:27:04.997 --> 00:27:06.164
Why not?

380
00:27:06.165 --> 00:27:08.624
I don't know. Your personality.

381
00:27:08.625 --> 00:27:11.586
When you commit to something...

382
00:27:11.587 --> 00:27:13.171
you focus all your energy there.

383
00:27:13.172 --> 00:27:14.672
Like a dog with a bone.

384
00:27:14.673 --> 00:27:17.175
Nice analogy.

385
00:27:17.176 --> 00:27:18.634
(CHUCKLING)
You know what I mean.

386
00:27:18.635 --> 00:27:22.471
When you give. it's 100
percent of 100 percent.

387
00:27:22.472 --> 00:27:25.516
If I was on to something.
it was just that thing.

388
00:27:25.517 --> 00:27:28.352
Even though I tell myself
I should change...

389
00:27:28.353 --> 00:27:31.772
I could never give it up.

390
00:27:31.773 --> 00:27:33.858
You gave us up. Mmm-mmm.

391
00:27:33.859 --> 00:27:35.985
No. neveL.

392
00:27:35.986 --> 00:27:37.987
Not in here.

393
00:27:37.988 --> 00:27:40.865
(POP MUSIC PLAYING)

394
00:27:40.866 --> 00:27:45.866
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

395
00:27:54.963 --> 00:27:59.963
Driver. turn left.

396
00:28:00.844 --> 00:28:04.347
Lennie. don't.

397
00:28:04.348 --> 00:28:04.848
What?

398
00:28:09.603 --> 00:28:10.978
Will you tell me
what's going on?

399
00:28:10.979 --> 00:28:15.979
It's okay.

400
00:28:17.236 --> 00:28:18.778
(HONKING IMPATIENTLY)

401
00:28:18.779 --> 00:28:23.779
Where is he?

402
00:28:24.743 --> 00:28:26.994
You see the gallery entrance
in the middle of the block?

403
00:28:26.995 --> 00:28:29.455
Will you tell me what's going on?
Do you see it?

404
00:28:29.456 --> 00:28:30.623
Yeah. I see it.

405
00:28:30.624 --> 00:28:32.375
When we stop.
I want you to get out

406
00:28:32.376 --> 00:28:34.168
of the car like
you're a shopper.

407
00:28:34.169 --> 00:28:35.586
I want you to go inside.

408
00:28:35.587 --> 00:28:36.879
Will you tell me
what's going on?

409
00:28:36.880 --> 00:28:38.089
Listen to me.

410
00:28:38.090 --> 00:28:39.548
Lennie. there's
no time for this.

411
00:28:39.549 --> 00:28:41.342
Just talk to me! Listen.

412
00:28:41.343 --> 00:28:44.262
When you exit the back of the
fabric store. turn right.

413
00:28:44.263 --> 00:28:46.013
Take the first
street on the right.

414
00:28:46.014 --> 00:28:47.807
then left on
the very next street.

415
00:28:47.808 --> 00:28:50.685
Go straight until you
come to a set of steps.

416
00:28:50.686 --> 00:28:54.146
There's a red corridor.
It's a lane.

417
00:28:54.147 --> 00:28:56.649
When you exit the lane.
there's a cab stand.

418
00:28:56.650 --> 00:28:58.067
Go back to the hotel.

419
00:28:58.068 --> 00:29:00.695
Get Kim. Get the head
of hotel security...

420
00:29:00.696 --> 00:29:03.572
and demand that he
cordon off your room.

421
00:29:03.573 --> 00:29:05.866
Do not open the door for anyone.

422
00:29:05.867 --> 00:29:08.953
No room service. no police. no one.
You wait for me.

423
00:29:08.954 --> 00:29:10.705
I can't believe
this is happening.

424
00:29:10.706 --> 00:29:15.584
I need you to focus.

425
00:29:15.585 --> 00:29:17.128
Are you ready?

426
00:29:17.129 --> 00:29:18.170
No.

427
00:29:18.171 --> 00:29:20.339
I need you to be ready.
I need you to be ready.

428
00:29:20.340 --> 00:29:21.632
Come on. focus.

429
00:29:21.633 --> 00:29:24.593
Driver. stop.

430
00:29:24.594 --> 00:29:25.928
Okay. go.

431
00:29:25.929 --> 00:29:27.555
Wait. what about you?

432
00:29:27.556 --> 00:29:28.723
I'll be fine.

433
00:29:28.724 --> 00:29:31.142
It's the guys following us who
are about to have a problem.

434
00:29:31.143 --> 00:29:33.477
When a dog has a bone...

435
00:29:33.478 --> 00:29:38.478
the last thing you want to do
is try and take it from him.

436
00:29:41.403 --> 00:29:46.324
Be careful.

437
00:29:46.325 --> 00:29:48.117
Out of the car.

438
00:29:48.118 --> 00:29:52.747
Come on. Move. move. move!

439
00:29:52.748 --> 00:29:54.206
(DIALING)

440
00:29:54.207 --> 00:29:56.584
Sir! Please.

441
00:29:56.585 --> 00:30:01.380
Please. Sir!

442
00:30:01.381 --> 00:30:03.090
He knows.

443
00:30:03.091 --> 00:30:04.925
Do it now.

444
00:30:04.926 --> 00:30:05.470
(HONKING)

445
00:30:23.653 --> 00:30:24.528
Come on.

446
00:30:24.529 --> 00:30:25.073
(HONKING)

447
00:30:38.794 --> 00:30:39.406
(BUZZING)

448
00:30:46.385 --> 00:30:46.885
Shit.

449
00:31:00.565 --> 00:31:05.565
Come on. Kim.
answer the goddamn phone.

450
00:31:27.592 --> 00:31:32.592
(GUNSHOTS)

451
00:31:37.060 --> 00:31:42.060
(CAR ALARM BEEPING)

452
00:31:52.617 --> 00:31:57.617
He's gone!

453
00:32:05.464 --> 00:32:08.048
Oh. God. no! Somebody help me!

454
00:32:08.049 --> 00:32:11.677
The key! Open the door. please!

455
00:32:11.678 --> 00:32:12.178
Shit!

456
00:32:46.296 --> 00:32:51.296
(SPEAKING TURKISH)

457
00:33:20.539 --> 00:33:25.539
(GROANING)

458
00:33:28.213 --> 00:33:28.825
(GUNSHOT)

459
00:33:35.887 --> 00:33:40.887
(GRUNTING)

460
00:33:59.619 --> 00:34:04.619
(GROANING)

461
00:34:23.560 --> 00:34:28.560
I'll blow his brains out.

462
00:34:29.232 --> 00:34:31.734
(LENORE GROANING)

463
00:34:31.735 --> 00:34:34.278
Oh. Bryan!

464
00:34:34.279 --> 00:34:35.612
Please!

465
00:34:35.613 --> 00:34:39.533
Drop the gun.

466
00:34:39.534 --> 00:34:40.951
(GIGGLING)

467
00:34:40.952 --> 00:34:42.536
<i>I really wish you were here.</i>

468
00:34:42.537 --> 00:34:46.457
Me too. You have no idea.
(PHONE BUZZING)

469
00:34:46.458 --> 00:34:47.916
<i>What?</i>

470
00:34:47.917 --> 00:34:49.084
<i>My dad's calling.</i>

471
00:34:49.085 --> 00:34:52.963
<i>He's on a date with my mom.</i>

472
00:34:52.964 --> 00:34:54.381
I'll call you right back.

473
00:34:54.382 --> 00:34:59.261
<i>Miss you. Bye.</i>

474
00:34:59.262 --> 00:35:00.471
How's it going?

475
00:35:00.472 --> 00:35:03.640
Listen to me carefully. Kim.

476
00:35:03.641 --> 00:35:06.393
Your mother and I...

477
00:35:06.394 --> 00:35:09.438
are going to be taken.

478
00:35:09.439 --> 00:35:10.773
Daddy!

479
00:35:10.774 --> 00:35:12.149
Oh. my God.

480
00:35:12.150 --> 00:35:14.401
And people are going to
come for you. too.

481
00:35:14.402 --> 00:35:17.154
<i>Leave the place
where you are calmly.</i>

482
00:35:17.155 --> 00:35:19.281
<i>Go to where the book
is I told you about.</i>

483
00:35:19.282 --> 00:35:22.993
There's a door. Go into the
room and hide in the closet.

484
00:35:22.994 --> 00:35:25.162
<i>You got that? Yes.</i>

485
00:35:25.163 --> 00:35:26.997
Good. I'll call you.

486
00:35:26.998 --> 00:35:30.459
Go. now.

487
00:35:30.460 --> 00:35:31.072
(BEEPING)

488
00:35:36.633 --> 00:35:41.470
(GASPING)

489
00:35:41.471 --> 00:35:43.806
LENORE: No!

490
00:35:43.807 --> 00:35:44.307
No!

491
00:35:54.150 --> 00:35:54.650
No!

492
00:36:13.044 --> 00:36:16.213
She is in room 422.

493
00:36:16.214 --> 00:36:17.631
LENORE: No! No!

494
00:36:17.632 --> 00:36:22.632
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

495
00:36:30.562 --> 00:36:32.271
(FAINT TICKING)

496
00:36:32.272 --> 00:36:35.399
<i>BRYAN: One. two. three...</i>

497
00:36:35.400 --> 00:36:39.695
<i>four. five. six.</i>

498
00:36:39.696 --> 00:36:40.821
<i>Right turn.</i>

499
00:36:40.822 --> 00:36:43.907
(MUEZZIN CALL TO PRAYER)

500
00:36:43.908 --> 00:36:48.908
<i>Man singing.</i>

501
00:36:54.627 --> 00:36:56.462
(TICKING)

502
00:36:56.463 --> 00:37:01.463
<i>One. two. three...</i>

503
00:37:02.051 --> 00:37:03.927
four. (S EAGU LLS CAWING)

504
00:37:03.928 --> 00:37:04.428
Boat.

505
00:37:15.064 --> 00:37:15.676
The pool!

506
00:37:26.618 --> 00:37:27.951
Security. fourth floor.

507
00:37:27.952 --> 00:37:29.453
<i>Do you copy me?</i>

508
00:37:29.454 --> 00:37:31.497
<i>Send someone now.</i>

509
00:37:31.498 --> 00:37:33.499
BRYAN: 25...

510
00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:36.793
26... 27...

511
00:37:36.794 --> 00:37:38.879
28... (BOAT HORN BLOWING)

512
00:37:38.880 --> 00:37:39.880
29.

513
00:37:39.881 --> 00:37:40.381
Stop.

514
00:37:48.973 --> 00:37:50.807
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

515
00:37:50.808 --> 00:37:51.850
She's not here.

516
00:37:51.851 --> 00:37:56.851
<i>- Not here?
- Check her dad's room.</i>

517
00:38:05.573 --> 00:38:06.185
(BEEPING)

518
00:38:20.880 --> 00:38:25.880
<i>BRYAN: Hammer on metal.</i>

519
00:38:35.061 --> 00:38:37.646
<i>Left. Gear shift to second.</i>

520
00:38:37.647 --> 00:38:40.315
<i>One. two. three. (TICKING)</i>

521
00:38:40.316 --> 00:38:42.150
(CHIRPING)

522
00:38:42.151 --> 00:38:44.486
Birds.

523
00:38:44.487 --> 00:38:47.030
(PLAYING TUNE)

524
00:38:47.031 --> 00:38:48.532
(CAR HONKING)

525
00:38:48.533 --> 00:38:53.370
(DOG BARKING)

526
00:38:53.371 --> 00:38:54.454
You have them?

527
00:38:54.455 --> 00:38:59.455
<i>SUKO: Yes. efendi.</i> Both.

528
00:39:00.378 --> 00:39:04.881
Take them to the shop.

529
00:39:04.882 --> 00:39:05.382
(YELP5)

530
00:39:24.736 --> 00:39:25.736
Look!

531
00:39:25.737 --> 00:39:30.737
A flip-flop.

532
00:39:31.909 --> 00:39:32.993
You go left!

533
00:39:32.994 --> 00:39:33.494
C'mon!

534
00:39:41.836 --> 00:39:43.337
(MUSIC PLAYING)

535
00:39:43.338 --> 00:39:44.588
<i>BRYAN: Right turn.</i>

536
00:39:44.589 --> 00:39:46.256
<i>Twenty-seven.</i>

537
00:39:46.257 --> 00:39:48.759
(WATCH CONTINUES TICKING)

538
00:39:48.760 --> 00:39:49.260
<i>StOP-</i>

539
00:39:55.975 --> 00:40:00.975
LENORE: No! No!

540
00:40:02.315 --> 00:40:07.315
(FOOTSTEPS)

541
00:40:46.025 --> 00:40:51.025
I shot some guy!

542
00:40:55.702 --> 00:41:00.702
(EXCLAIMS) (ALARM RINGING)

543
00:41:06.337 --> 00:41:09.673
(MOANING SOFTLY)

544
00:41:09.674 --> 00:41:14.674
(MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY)

545
00:41:21.477 --> 00:41:26.477
(MUSIC PLAYING)

546
00:42:11.402 --> 00:42:16.402
(GROANING)

547
00:42:18.242 --> 00:42:20.368
Come on. Sam. Pick up.

548
00:42:20.369 --> 00:42:21.495
(PHONE RINGING)

549
00:42:21.496 --> 00:42:23.955
<i>Hey. this is Sam.
Leave me a message.</i>

550
00:42:23.956 --> 00:42:24.456
Shit.

551
00:42:29.587 --> 00:42:33.256
(PHONE BUZZING)

552
00:42:33.257 --> 00:42:34.591
Are you guys Okay?

553
00:42:34.592 --> 00:42:37.093
No. no. Are you all right?

554
00:42:37.094 --> 00:42:38.595
Yes.

555
00:42:38.596 --> 00:42:40.764
I'm just scared.

556
00:42:40.765 --> 00:42:44.100
Kim. listen to me
very carefully.

557
00:42:44.101 --> 00:42:46.937
(SOBBING) I need you to calm
down and pull yourself together.

558
00:42:46.938 --> 00:42:47.938
<i>Okay-</i>

559
00:42:47.939 --> 00:42:51.149
The men who came for you.
did they leave?

560
00:42:51.150 --> 00:42:53.985
Yes. What do they want?

561
00:42:53.986 --> 00:42:55.612
I'm going to find out.

562
00:42:55.613 --> 00:43:00.283
Is Mom okay?

563
00:43:00.284 --> 00:43:02.118
Dad.

564
00:43:02.119 --> 00:43:03.453
Mom's fine.

565
00:43:03.454 --> 00:43:05.372
<i>Okay-</i>

566
00:43:05.373 --> 00:43:07.290
What are we going to do?

567
00:43:07.291 --> 00:43:10.794
I want you to go to the U.S. Embassy.
You'll be safe there.

568
00:43:10.795 --> 00:43:14.005
What about you and Mom?

569
00:43:14.006 --> 00:43:17.300
I'll figure something out.

570
00:43:17.301 --> 00:43:18.718
Where are you now?

571
00:43:18.719 --> 00:43:20.971
I don't really know. Kim.

572
00:43:20.972 --> 00:43:23.181
<i>Dad. how can I tell them
where to find you. then?</i>

573
00:43:23.182 --> 00:43:25.183
You can't. Now get going.

574
00:43:25.184 --> 00:43:26.476
No.

575
00:43:26.477 --> 00:43:27.477
Kimmie...

576
00:43:27.478 --> 00:43:30.522
No. Tell me what to do.

577
00:43:30.523 --> 00:43:31.523
No. Kim.

578
00:43:31.524 --> 00:43:33.817
Dad. if you tell me what
to do. I can do it.

579
00:43:33.818 --> 00:43:34.985
Kim. this is not a game.

580
00:43:34.986 --> 00:43:38.655
I know that.
It's my parents' lives.

581
00:43:38.656 --> 00:43:40.490
<i>Dad. please.</i>

582
00:43:40.491 --> 00:43:45.491
You're wasting time.

583
00:43:46.831 --> 00:43:48.164
<i>Please.</i>

584
00:43:48.165 --> 00:43:51.167
Tell me what to do.

585
00:43:51.168 --> 00:43:56.168
Can you get out of
the closet safely?

586
00:43:59.010 --> 00:44:00.844
Yes.

587
00:44:00.845 --> 00:44:04.848
If you can.
take the case with you.

588
00:44:04.849 --> 00:44:05.349
<i>Okay-</i>

589
00:44:17.028 --> 00:44:18.028
I'm out.

590
00:44:18.029 --> 00:44:23.029
The combination is 23-28-84.

591
00:44:30.458 --> 00:44:31.791
<i>Is it open?</i> Yeah.

592
00:44:31.792 --> 00:44:33.710
Okay. Do you see a map?

593
00:44:33.711 --> 00:44:34.586
Yeah.

594
00:44:34.587 --> 00:44:35.962
<i>Take the map.</i>

595
00:44:35.963 --> 00:44:38.465
You'll see a scale
onthetop in kilometers.

596
00:44:38.466 --> 00:44:41.551
<i>Do you see it?</i>

597
00:44:41.552 --> 00:44:43.261
Yeah. I see it.

598
00:44:43.262 --> 00:44:45.764
Take a shoelace from one
of my shoes in the closet.

599
00:44:45.765 --> 00:44:50.727
<i>Use it as a guide.</i>

600
00:44:50.728 --> 00:44:52.228
<i>There's a pen in the case.</i>

601
00:44:52.229 --> 00:44:54.606
<i>Take it.</i>

602
00:44:54.607 --> 00:44:59.444
Draw a circle with the
hotel in the center of it.

603
00:44:59.445 --> 00:45:00.403
<i>It's done.</i>

604
00:45:00.404 --> 00:45:03.406
Make the diameter
three kilometers.

605
00:45:03.407 --> 00:45:08.407
<i>You got that?</i>

606
00:45:13.000 --> 00:45:14.000
<i>It's done.</i>

607
00:45:14.001 --> 00:45:18.922
Draw another circle with
the market in the center.

608
00:45:18.923 --> 00:45:19.673
<i>Okay-</i>

609
00:45:19.674 --> 00:45:21.758
Do the circles
intersect at any points?

610
00:45:21.759 --> 00:45:24.636
<i>No.</i>

611
00:45:24.637 --> 00:45:26.346
Now. take one of
those little cans.

612
00:45:26.347 --> 00:45:28.431
<i>the ones with
the pins on the top.</i>

613
00:45:28.432 --> 00:45:29.432
<i>It's a grenade.</i>

614
00:45:29.433 --> 00:45:33.770
I want you to go to the
balcony with the grenade.

615
00:45:33.771 --> 00:45:38.771
<i>Is there a safe place
you can throw it?</i>

616
00:45:39.652 --> 00:45:41.027
There's a parking garage.

617
00:45:41.028 --> 00:45:42.862
Anyone on it?

618
00:45:42.863 --> 00:45:43.863
KIM: No.

619
00:45:43.864 --> 00:45:45.865
I want you to pull the pin
out of the grenade...

620
00:45:45.866 --> 00:45:47.534
<i>count to three so I can hearit.</i>

621
00:45:47.535 --> 00:45:49.285
then toss it as far as you can.

622
00:45:49.286 --> 00:45:51.162
<i>And then run back into the room.</i>

623
00:45:51.163 --> 00:45:56.163
Keep the phone on so I
can hear the explosion.

624
00:45:56.544 --> 00:45:57.794
One...

625
00:45:57.795 --> 00:45:58.878
<i>two...</i>

626
00:45:58.879 --> 00:45:59.379
three.

627
00:46:08.139 --> 00:46:11.182
One. two. three...

628
00:46:11.183 --> 00:46:14.978
(MUFFLED EXPLOSION)

629
00:46:14.979 --> 00:46:15.979
Dad?

630
00:46:15.980 --> 00:46:19.524
Now draw a circle on the map
with the hotel in the middle...

631
00:46:19.525 --> 00:46:24.525
and the circumference
at 4.5 kilometers.

632
00:46:29.994 --> 00:46:33.204
Do the circles
intersect at any points?

633
00:46:33.205 --> 00:46:34.914
Yeah. at two points.

634
00:46:34.915 --> 00:46:37.042
I'm at one of the two
intersecting points.

635
00:46:37.043 --> 00:46:41.588
Now go outside and look at
the flags on the rooftops.

636
00:46:41.589 --> 00:46:45.175
<i>Do you see the flags?</i>

637
00:46:45.176 --> 00:46:48.011
Yes. Are they in the wind?

638
00:46:48.012 --> 00:46:52.057
Yeah. Going east. right?

639
00:46:52.058 --> 00:46:53.683
I think so. yeah.
How did you know?

640
00:46:53.684 --> 00:46:54.893
Now look at the map.

641
00:46:54.894 --> 00:46:59.022
I want you to go to the point where
the circles intersect at the east.

642
00:46:59.023 --> 00:47:00.690
I want you to take
one of the guns.

643
00:47:00.691 --> 00:47:02.525
<i>get to a rooftop.
wait for my call.</i>

644
00:47:02.526 --> 00:47:04.027
And two of the grenades.

645
00:47:04.028 --> 00:47:08.865
Go to the rooftop at
the most easterly point.

646
00:47:08.866 --> 00:47:10.450
Get up to the rooftop.

647
00:47:10.451 --> 00:47:12.368
<i>Wait for my call.</i>

648
00:47:12.369 --> 00:47:15.121
Be casual. Kim. Blend in.

649
00:47:15.122 --> 00:47:19.042
<i>Okay.</i> (METAL CLANGING)

650
00:47:19.043 --> 00:47:22.378
Dad?

651
00:47:22.379 --> 00:47:25.048
<i>Dad?</i>

652
00:47:25.049 --> 00:47:25.661
(BEEPING)

653
00:47:31.055 --> 00:47:36.055
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

654
00:48:27.528 --> 00:48:29.279
Who are you?

655
00:48:29.280 --> 00:48:31.698
Those clothes don't belong to you.

656
00:48:31.699 --> 00:48:33.283
Help!

657
00:48:33.284 --> 00:48:38.284
There's a thief in here!

658
00:48:40.499 --> 00:48:45.499
(SIRENS WAILING)

659
00:48:52.636 --> 00:48:57.636
(DOOR OPENING)

660
00:49:38.599 --> 00:49:43.599
You know this man?

661
00:49:47.358 --> 00:49:50.109
This one?

662
00:49:50.110 --> 00:49:52.195
This one?

663
00:49:52.196 --> 00:49:54.447
No.

664
00:49:54.448 --> 00:49:57.116
This one?

665
00:49:57.117 --> 00:49:58.284
What do you want?

666
00:49:58.285 --> 00:50:00.036
You recognize none of them.

667
00:50:00.037 --> 00:50:01.704
To you. they were nothing.

668
00:50:01.705 --> 00:50:05.041
But to other people...

669
00:50:05.042 --> 00:50:08.962
they are sons and grandsons.

670
00:50:08.963 --> 00:50:11.381
Fathers and husbands.

671
00:50:11.382 --> 00:50:14.884
And you killed them all.

672
00:50:14.885 --> 00:50:19.885
Like they were so many nothings.

673
00:50:23.894 --> 00:50:27.397
(WHISPERING) And this one?

674
00:50:27.398 --> 00:50:29.482
You recognize him?

675
00:50:29.483 --> 00:50:32.068
You do recognize him.

676
00:50:32.069 --> 00:50:35.571
Him. you didn't just kill.
Him. you strapped to a chair.

677
00:50:35.572 --> 00:50:38.449
You attached electric
cables to the chair.

678
00:50:38.450 --> 00:50:40.493
You turned the current on...

679
00:50:40.494 --> 00:50:44.330
and you left it on
until his heart burst.

680
00:50:44.331 --> 00:50:48.960
He's the one who kidnapped dozens
of girls and ruined their lives.

681
00:50:48.961 --> 00:50:51.629
He was my son.

682
00:50:51.630 --> 00:50:55.883
Marko. from Tropojé.

683
00:50:55.884 --> 00:51:00.138
And I have come to
take you to Tropojé...

684
00:51:00.139 --> 00:51:03.933
to face you to the people
whose lives you have ruined.

685
00:51:03.934 --> 00:51:05.309
To give them justice.

686
00:51:05.310 --> 00:51:07.186
You mean to give them revenge.

687
00:51:07.187 --> 00:51:11.899
It if gives us peace
call it anything you wish.

688
00:51:11.900 --> 00:51:16.900
I killed your son because
he kidnapped my daughter.

689
00:51:17.489 --> 00:51:21.325
I don't care what he did!

690
00:51:21.326 --> 00:51:23.369
I only know...

691
00:51:23.370 --> 00:51:26.414
I will never see his face again.

692
00:51:26.415 --> 00:51:29.751
I will never hear his voice.

693
00:51:29.752 --> 00:51:30.296
(KISSES)

694
00:51:34.339 --> 00:51:37.425
And as you held him responsible
for your daughter...

695
00:51:37.426 --> 00:51:41.012
I hold you responsible for him.

696
00:51:41.013 --> 00:51:43.473
Your death will not be quick.

697
00:51:43.474 --> 00:51:45.308
It will not be pleasant.

698
00:51:45.309 --> 00:51:46.768
But before you die...

699
00:51:46.769 --> 00:51:49.604
this is what you will see.

700
00:51:49.605 --> 00:51:54.605
Bring herin.

701
00:51:54.985 --> 00:51:59.985
(GROANING)

702
00:52:00.991 --> 00:52:05.991
Bryan... (KNIFE CLICKS OPEN)

703
00:52:10.501 --> 00:52:14.837
(CRIES OUT)

704
00:52:14.838 --> 00:52:19.838
(MUFFLED GROANING)

705
00:52:24.306 --> 00:52:26.849
(LOUD GROANING)

706
00:52:26.850 --> 00:52:30.645
How long will it take for the
blood to rush to her head...

707
00:52:30.646 --> 00:52:35.399
and have no place to go?

708
00:52:35.400 --> 00:52:37.819
About 30 minutes.

709
00:52:37.820 --> 00:52:40.696
You are right.
You're an expert for this.

710
00:52:40.697 --> 00:52:43.241
So you have 30 minutes
to watch her die.

711
00:52:43.242 --> 00:52:45.868
She had nothing to do with this.

712
00:52:45.869 --> 00:52:48.037
Do what you wantwith me.
Let her go.

713
00:52:48.038 --> 00:52:49.872
Don't play the hero with me.

714
00:52:49.873 --> 00:52:51.958
Now we are going to
catch your daughter.

715
00:52:51.959 --> 00:52:55.378
She will be sold to the
lowest brothel in this world.

716
00:52:55.379 --> 00:52:57.004
LENORE: No! No!

717
00:52:57.005 --> 00:53:00.466
She will be abused
by so many men...

718
00:53:00.467 --> 00:53:05.467
that she'll be nothing more than a
piece of meat a dog would not have.

719
00:53:18.819 --> 00:53:20.027
(LENORE SOBBING)

720
00:53:20.028 --> 00:53:22.321
Don't listen to them. Lennie.

721
00:53:22.322 --> 00:53:23.489
Kim is safe.

722
00:53:23.490 --> 00:53:25.032
I spoke with her.

723
00:53:25.033 --> 00:53:26.617
She's safe.

724
00:53:26.618 --> 00:53:29.495
You have to stay calm.
Breathe slowly.

725
00:53:29.496 --> 00:53:30.663
You have to.

726
00:53:30.664 --> 00:53:32.999
I won't let anything
happen to you. or to her.

727
00:53:33.000 --> 00:53:37.420
I promise.

728
00:53:37.421 --> 00:53:38.754
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

729
00:53:38.755 --> 00:53:39.922
(MEN TALKING EXCITEDLY)

730
00:53:39.923 --> 00:53:41.716
MAN: <i>Hello. Murad? Shh!</i>

731
00:53:41.717 --> 00:53:42.884
Quiet.

732
00:53:42.885 --> 00:53:45.386
<i>We lost the girl.</i>

733
00:53:45.387 --> 00:53:46.596
The girl has gone.

734
00:53:46.597 --> 00:53:49.182
I'll be back as soon as
we get her. then we move.

735
00:53:49.183 --> 00:53:50.558
Come on!

736
00:53:50.559 --> 00:53:51.767
(LENORE GROANING)

737
00:53:51.768 --> 00:53:56.768
Hold on. Lennie.

738
00:54:15.083 --> 00:54:17.126
Hold on. Lennie. Hold on.

739
00:54:17.127 --> 00:54:17.671
(HONKING)

740
00:54:22.633 --> 00:54:25.635
What's he doing?

741
00:54:25.636 --> 00:54:28.095
Get out of the way!

742
00:54:28.096 --> 00:54:29.931
Sorry! Sorry!

743
00:54:29.932 --> 00:54:34.932
Come back! You have to pay!

744
00:54:35.103 --> 00:54:37.730
Lennie.

745
00:54:37.731 --> 00:54:38.231
Lennie.

746
00:54:48.158 --> 00:54:53.158
I'm with you. baby.
I'm here. I'm here.

747
00:55:15.185 --> 00:55:18.104
Come on. Call.

748
00:55:18.105 --> 00:55:21.023
Please. come on.

749
00:55:21.024 --> 00:55:21.983
Lennie.

750
00:55:21.984 --> 00:55:22.942
Bryan.

751
00:55:22.943 --> 00:55:25.194
Lennie. Lennie.

752
00:55:25.195 --> 00:55:30.195
I'm coming back.

753
00:55:38.625 --> 00:55:39.709
Please.

754
00:55:39.710 --> 00:55:41.168
(PHONE BUZZING) I'm here.

755
00:55:41.169 --> 00:55:46.169
Set off another grenade.

756
00:55:56.018 --> 00:56:01.018
(EXPLOSION)

757
00:56:01.398 --> 00:56:03.441
Dad? You're close.

758
00:56:03.442 --> 00:56:05.651
I want you to keep moving east.

759
00:56:05.652 --> 00:56:08.195
Count to 30 and then
set off another one.

760
00:56:08.196 --> 00:56:13.196
One. two. three...

761
00:56:14.953 --> 00:56:15.497
18.19...

762
00:56:19.583 --> 00:56:21.500
26. 27...

763
00:56:21.501 --> 00:56:24.045
28. 29...

764
00:56:24.046 --> 00:56:26.797
30.

765
00:56:26.798 --> 00:56:31.177
(EXPLOSION)

766
00:56:31.178 --> 00:56:36.178
Go out and check
what's going on.

767
00:56:40.228 --> 00:56:42.229
<i>Kim. Yeah.</i>

768
00:56:42.230 --> 00:56:47.230
Look east. Look for a
white cloud of steam.

769
00:56:47.611 --> 00:56:48.778
I see it.

770
00:56:48.779 --> 00:56:53.779
Run to it. Tell me
when you're there.

771
00:57:00.123 --> 00:57:05.123
I'm going down.

772
00:57:18.225 --> 00:57:20.101
Dad. Where are you?

773
00:57:20.102 --> 00:57:21.268
I'm right by the steam.

774
00:57:21.269 --> 00:57:23.312
<i>Drop the gun down the vent.</i>

775
00:57:23.313 --> 00:57:25.147
Oh. God. they're here.
They're coming.

776
00:57:25.148 --> 00:57:29.693
Drop the gun. Kim. and run.

777
00:57:29.694 --> 00:57:30.820
Go.

778
00:57:30.821 --> 00:57:35.821
<i>Dad! They're coming.</i>

779
00:57:37.536 --> 00:57:42.536
(MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

780
00:57:44.418 --> 00:57:49.418
(CHAIN RATTLING)

781
00:58:05.856 --> 00:58:10.856
I'm coming back.

782
00:58:15.240 --> 00:58:20.240
(TALKING EXCITEDLY)

783
00:58:40.056 --> 00:58:45.056
(SCREAMS) (GUNSHOT)

784
00:59:03.455 --> 00:59:08.455
(COCKS GUN)

785
00:59:37.155 --> 00:59:42.155
(GROANING)

786
01:00:00.804 --> 01:00:04.473
Drop that.

787
01:00:04.474 --> 01:00:09.228
On your knees!

788
01:00:09.229 --> 01:00:10.771
Don't do this.

789
01:00:10.772 --> 01:00:13.315
Please.

790
01:00:13.316 --> 01:00:18.316
(GUNSHOTS)

791
01:00:23.159 --> 01:00:25.327
Dad? (SOBBING)

792
01:00:25.328 --> 01:00:28.831
Dad! Dad!

793
01:00:28.832 --> 01:00:29.332
<i>BabY-</i>

794
01:00:34.587 --> 01:00:35.796
Where's Mom? Is she okay?

795
01:00:35.797 --> 01:00:40.509
She's safe. She's safe.

796
01:00:40.510 --> 01:00:41.122
(WEEPING)

797
01:00:48.518 --> 01:00:53.518
Slow down. slow down. slow down.

798
01:00:53.732 --> 01:00:58.732
I've got a fare.

799
01:01:00.488 --> 01:01:04.116
I'll be back.

800
01:01:04.117 --> 01:01:09.117
(CALLS OUT IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

801
01:01:10.373 --> 01:01:12.583
That man had the same
tattoo as the men in Paris.

802
01:01:12.584 --> 01:01:17.584
It's not you they want. Kim.
It's me.

803
01:01:30.643 --> 01:01:33.270
I want you to wait here.
I'm going to get Mom.

804
01:01:33.271 --> 01:01:35.564
Wait five minutes.
and if I don't show up...

805
01:01:35.565 --> 01:01:39.735
I want you to go straight here.
to the American Embassy.

806
01:01:39.736 --> 01:01:41.737
Tell them what happened. Dad...

807
01:01:41.738 --> 01:01:43.614
No time. Kim.
Give me your phone.

808
01:01:43.615 --> 01:01:46.617
You wait five minutes.
not a moment longer.

809
01:01:46.618 --> 01:01:49.286
No matter what happens.
time runs out. you go.

810
01:01:49.287 --> 01:01:51.580
You understand me?

811
01:01:51.581 --> 01:01:52.081
<i>Okay-</i>

812
01:02:24.447 --> 01:02:29.447
(MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

813
01:02:40.463 --> 01:02:41.075
(MOANING)

814
01:03:05.780 --> 01:03:10.780
(SIREN WAILING)

815
01:03:25.884 --> 01:03:28.927
(LENORE SHOUTING WEAKLY)

816
01:03:28.928 --> 01:03:31.346
No!

817
01:03:31.347 --> 01:03:33.432
No.

818
01:03:33.433 --> 01:03:33.933
Bryan!

819
01:03:51.075 --> 01:03:53.702
(PHONE RINGING)

820
01:03:53.703 --> 01:03:54.203
Yes?

821
01:03:59.292 --> 01:04:03.879
(PHONE BEEPING)

822
01:04:03.880 --> 01:04:08.880
(METAL DOOR OPENING)

823
01:04:21.105 --> 01:04:21.980
Move!

824
01:04:21.981 --> 01:04:23.899
You killed him.
I had no choice. Move.

825
01:04:23.900 --> 01:04:26.109
Where's Mom? She's
fine. she's not far.

826
01:04:26.110 --> 01:04:30.572
Where is she? Come on. move!

827
01:04:30.573 --> 01:04:32.241
I don't want to do this.
Keep going. Kim.

828
01:04:32.242 --> 01:04:33.242
Where are we going?

829
01:04:33.243 --> 01:04:38.243
Go straight. We have
to go to the Embassy.

830
01:04:38.248 --> 01:04:39.623
I'm not sure I can.

831
01:04:39.624 --> 01:04:41.583
Do you know how to shoot? No.

832
01:04:41.584 --> 01:04:46.584
Then drive.

833
01:04:49.968 --> 01:04:54.096
They escaped.

834
01:04:54.097 --> 01:04:55.806
<i>Officer down in Balat.</i>

835
01:04:55.807 --> 01:04:57.641
COPY-

836
01:04:57.642 --> 01:04:58.600
Shit. cops.

837
01:04:58.601 --> 01:05:00.185
(SIREN WAILING)

838
01:05:00.186 --> 01:05:01.103
I have to stop.

839
01:05:01.104 --> 01:05:06.104
No. I just shot one of them.
Now. go.

840
01:05:09.612 --> 01:05:11.488
(CRYING OUT)

841
01:05:11.489 --> 01:05:15.450
Come on. go!

842
01:05:15.451 --> 01:05:20.451
(SIRENS WAILING)

843
01:05:35.638 --> 01:05:36.138
Right.

844
01:05:41.978 --> 01:05:44.479
Back. back. back!

845
01:05:44.480 --> 01:05:48.233
Come on. move!

846
01:05:48.234 --> 01:05:53.234
Come on. Kim.

847
01:05:57.160 --> 01:06:00.078
GO. go!

848
01:06:00.079 --> 01:06:05.079
Faster. (TIRES SCREECHING)

849
01:06:05.168 --> 01:06:10.168
Keep going.

850
01:06:18.514 --> 01:06:22.559
Left! Yeah.

851
01:06:22.560 --> 01:06:26.521
They're in the taxi!

852
01:06:26.522 --> 01:06:30.192
Keep going.

853
01:06:30.193 --> 01:06:31.360
Oh. no. Shit.

854
01:06:31.361 --> 01:06:36.361
Stay low. Keep going.

855
01:06:37.283 --> 01:06:38.909
Come on. faster. I can't.

856
01:06:38.910 --> 01:06:42.579
You can do it! I can't!

857
01:06:42.580 --> 01:06:45.415
Come on. move! Move. (HONKING)

858
01:06:45.416 --> 01:06:47.084
Dad! Keep 90ing_.

859
01:06:47.085 --> 01:06:49.044
KIM: Move!

860
01:06:49.045 --> 01:06:49.545
Right.

861
01:07:02.100 --> 01:07:05.811
Oh. shit.

862
01:07:05.812 --> 01:07:06.312
No!

863
01:07:17.407 --> 01:07:17.951
(HONKING)

864
01:07:29.085 --> 01:07:33.964
Come on. Kim. Move!

865
01:07:33.965 --> 01:07:38.965
"M trying. Go!"

866
01:07:43.391 --> 01:07:47.227
Come on. keep going.

867
01:07:47.228 --> 01:07:52.228
Turn left.

868
01:07:55.820 --> 01:07:57.571
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

869
01:07:57.572 --> 01:08:00.198
Shit.

870
01:08:00.199 --> 01:08:01.241
Dad!

871
01:08:01.242 --> 01:08:06.242
Keep going. Stay low.

872
01:08:15.673 --> 01:08:18.008
Faster. Kim. I can't.

873
01:08:18.009 --> 01:08:22.929
(HORN BLARING)

874
01:08:22.930 --> 01:08:24.389
Come on. faster! Dad!

875
01:08:24.390 --> 01:08:29.227
Keep going.

876
01:08:29.228 --> 01:08:31.730
You can make it. (HORN BLARING)

877
01:08:31.731 --> 01:08:32.231
Do it.

878
01:08:52.668 --> 01:08:56.963
(TIRES SQUEALING)

879
01:08:56.964 --> 01:08:58.632
Here! Don't stop.

880
01:08:58.633 --> 01:08:59.716
But the soldiers.

881
01:08:59.717 --> 01:09:01.801
They'll move.

882
01:09:01.802 --> 01:09:03.595
(GUNS COCKING)

883
01:09:03.596 --> 01:09:08.596
Down. Kim!

884
01:09:21.489 --> 01:09:23.907
(ALARM BLARING)

885
01:09:23.908 --> 01:09:25.242
MAN ON P.A.: <i>Nobody</i> shoot.

886
01:09:25.243 --> 01:09:30.243
<i>It's a suicide bomber.</i>

887
01:09:30.957 --> 01:09:32.916
Are you okay?

888
01:09:32.917 --> 01:09:33.417
Yeah.

889
01:09:37.004 --> 01:09:42.004
Keep your head down. Kimmie.

890
01:09:46.806 --> 01:09:47.806
Hey. Bry.

891
01:09:47.807 --> 01:09:51.184
<i>Sam. we 're in a courtyard of the U.
S. Embassy in Istanbul...</i>

892
01:09:51.185 --> 01:09:52.894
in a smashed-up car.

893
01:09:52.895 --> 01:09:53.895
<i>Don't ask.</i>

894
01:09:53.896 --> 01:09:56.356
Can you call someone to make
sure we don't get shot?

895
01:09:56.357 --> 01:09:57.566
Yeah. of course.

896
01:09:57.567 --> 01:09:59.192
<i>Thanks.</i>

897
01:09:59.193 --> 01:10:03.822
It's Bry. He's in
trouble in Istanbul.

898
01:10:03.823 --> 01:10:08.493
Mom didn't get away. did she?

899
01:10:08.494 --> 01:10:09.661
No.

900
01:10:09.662 --> 01:10:11.496
(SOBBING) Oh. God. Dad.

901
01:10:11.497 --> 01:10:12.956
Tell me the truth. Is she...

902
01:10:12.957 --> 01:10:16.668
No. no. no. Kim. No. she's not.

903
01:10:16.669 --> 01:10:20.046
But they have her.

904
01:10:20.047 --> 01:10:24.342
And they will use her until
they get what they want.

905
01:10:24.343 --> 01:10:27.721
Me.

906
01:10:27.722 --> 01:10:31.600
You'll be safe here in the
Embassy until I come back.

907
01:10:31.601 --> 01:10:34.185
Kimmie. it's going to be okay.

908
01:10:34.186 --> 01:10:36.855
Nothing's okay.

909
01:10:36.856 --> 01:10:40.942
Kim. listen.

910
01:10:40.943 --> 01:10:43.528
I have to find them...

911
01:10:43.529 --> 01:10:45.405
and bring your mom back.

912
01:10:45.406 --> 01:10:47.157
And then I have to
make sure these people

913
01:10:47.158 --> 01:10:50.243
never bother us
again in our lives.

914
01:10:50.244 --> 01:10:55.244
What are you going to do?

915
01:10:56.083 --> 01:11:01.083
What I do best.

916
01:11:05.468 --> 01:11:10.468
(KIM SOBBING)

917
01:11:29.909 --> 01:11:33.161
Mrs. Mills.

918
01:11:33.162 --> 01:11:36.790
What should I do
with you. Mrs. Mills?

919
01:11:36.791 --> 01:11:41.791
(MUEZZIN CALL TO PRAYER)

920
01:11:44.298 --> 01:11:49.298
(MUSIC PLAYING)

921
01:12:35.182 --> 01:12:37.600
I have nothing against you.

922
01:12:37.601 --> 01:12:42.601
You didn't kill my son.

923
01:12:43.649 --> 01:12:48.611
But your husband did.

924
01:12:48.612 --> 01:12:51.448
Now. he betrayed you by choosing

925
01:12:51.449 --> 01:12:55.326
to save your daughter
instead of you.

926
01:12:55.327 --> 01:12:59.831
He left you here like a dog.

927
01:12:59.832 --> 01:13:04.832
At least my daughter
is still alive.

928
01:13:06.380 --> 01:13:11.380
(MUEZZIN CALL TO PRAYER)

929
01:13:19.935 --> 01:13:24.689
Mrs. Mills.
you're a good mother...

930
01:13:24.690 --> 01:13:28.193
and a brave woman.

931
01:13:28.194 --> 01:13:31.946
Forthat I'm going to
send you back home...

932
01:13:31.947 --> 01:13:36.947
piece by piece.

933
01:13:38.871 --> 01:13:41.664
(SHIP HORN BLOWING)

934
01:13:41.665 --> 01:13:46.665
(S EAGU LLS CAWING)

935
01:14:13.948 --> 01:14:18.948
(HAMMER TAPPING)

936
01:14:35.010 --> 01:14:40.010
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

937
01:15:11.213 --> 01:15:16.213
(PLAYING TUNE)

938
01:15:38.407 --> 01:15:43.407
(DOG BARKING)

939
01:16:12.274 --> 01:16:12.886
(CHOKING)

940
01:16:26.580 --> 01:16:31.580
(BARKING CONTINUES)

941
01:16:35.798 --> 01:16:40.798
(MUSIC PLAYING)

942
01:16:52.064 --> 01:16:53.898
(BARKING)

943
01:16:53.899 --> 01:16:56.109
Shut up!

944
01:16:56.110 --> 01:17:01.110
(DOG WHINING)

945
01:17:04.493 --> 01:17:09.493
(GRUNTING)

946
01:17:13.168 --> 01:17:17.213
(COCKS GUN)

947
01:17:17.214 --> 01:17:22.214
(DOG BARKING LOUDLY)

948
01:17:44.533 --> 01:17:49.533
Ohri. shoot this dog.

949
01:17:54.501 --> 01:17:55.113
(GUNFIRE)

950
01:18:06.305 --> 01:18:11.305
Go and see what's happened.

951
01:18:17.649 --> 01:18:20.401
Let's go. Move through
here. to the hammam.

952
01:18:20.402 --> 01:18:20.902
Hurry!

953
01:19:02.111 --> 01:19:03.778
(GUNS COCKING)

954
01:19:03.779 --> 01:19:08.779
(GUNSHOTS)

955
01:19:31.557 --> 01:19:32.974
Mirko!

956
01:19:32.975 --> 01:19:33.475
Mirko!

957
01:19:37.312 --> 01:19:40.481
You stay here.

958
01:19:40.482 --> 01:19:45.482
LENORE: No!

959
01:20:18.187 --> 01:20:21.814
(BOTH GRUNTING)

960
01:20:21.815 --> 01:20:22.315
No.

961
01:20:35.370 --> 01:20:35.982
(GUNSHOT)

962
01:20:50.385 --> 01:20:55.385
(LENORE GROANING)

963
01:20:56.642 --> 01:20:59.393
(GUNFIRE)

964
01:20:59.394 --> 01:21:01.229
No. Bryan!

965
01:21:01.230 --> 01:21:06.230
MURAD: Come on!

966
01:21:15.619 --> 01:21:20.619
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

967
01:21:33.303 --> 01:21:37.765
(MAN GRUMBLING IN TURKISH)

968
01:21:37.766 --> 01:21:39.392
You can't come in!

969
01:21:39.393 --> 01:21:40.005
Get lost.

970
01:22:01.123 --> 01:22:06.123
(SCRAPING)

971
01:22:30.402 --> 01:22:30.902
Lennie.

972
01:22:49.338 --> 01:22:54.338
(GRUNTING)

973
01:22:56.345 --> 01:22:56.957
(YELLING)

974
01:23:17.866 --> 01:23:22.866
(GRUNTING)

975
01:24:10.085 --> 01:24:12.253
(GROANING)

976
01:24:12.254 --> 01:24:17.254
(KNIFE CLATTERS)

977
01:24:26.476 --> 01:24:27.088
(YELLING)

978
01:24:41.616 --> 01:24:46.616
(BREATHING HARD)

979
01:25:15.150 --> 01:25:17.484
Lennie.

980
01:25:17.485 --> 01:25:19.069
(COUGHING)

981
01:25:19.070 --> 01:25:21.238
I'm here. baby. I'm here.

982
01:25:21.239 --> 01:25:24.408
I'm coming back. Lennie.
I'm coming back.

983
01:25:24.409 --> 01:25:24.909
Okay?

984
01:25:39.257 --> 01:25:44.257
(PHONE RINGING)

985
01:25:49.809 --> 01:25:54.809
(RINGING GETTING LOUDER)

986
01:26:04.532 --> 01:26:07.701
What are you waiting for?

987
01:26:07.702 --> 01:26:10.871
You have other sons?

988
01:26:10.872 --> 01:26:11.872
Two.

989
01:26:11.873 --> 01:26:16.873
And if I killed you. they
will come and seek revenge.

990
01:26:17.420 --> 01:26:19.755
They will. for sure.

991
01:26:19.756 --> 01:26:23.342
And I will kill them. too.

992
01:26:23.343 --> 01:26:25.552
You can change that.

993
01:26:25.553 --> 01:26:28.722
You can go home. live your life.

994
01:26:28.723 --> 01:26:32.935
Enjoy your sons. your grandsons.

995
01:26:32.936 --> 01:26:35.896
And my other son...

996
01:26:35.897 --> 01:26:36.397
Marko.

997
01:26:40.944 --> 01:26:44.154
The son you killed.

998
01:26:44.155 --> 01:26:47.408
Am I supposed to just forget it?

999
01:26:47.409 --> 01:26:48.409
No.

1000
01:26:48.410 --> 01:26:50.744
You will just have
to live with it.

1001
01:26:50.745 --> 01:26:54.415
like the parents of all
those kidnapped girls.

1002
01:26:54.416 --> 01:26:57.251
Or you can die here.

1003
01:26:57.252 --> 01:26:58.460
What are you telling me?

1004
01:26:58.461 --> 01:27:03.461
What I'm saying is.
if you give me your word...

1005
01:27:04.426 --> 01:27:09.426
I will throw down this gun
and simply walk away.

1006
01:27:11.391 --> 01:27:13.058
Why?

1007
01:27:13.059 --> 01:27:18.059
Because I am tired of it all.

1008
01:27:23.945 --> 01:27:24.557
(SIGHING)

1009
01:27:45.717 --> 01:27:50.717
(GUN CLICKS)

1010
01:28:25.799 --> 01:28:28.926
Lennie. I'm here.

1011
01:28:28.927 --> 01:28:31.887
I'm here. baby. I'm here.

1012
01:28:31.888 --> 01:28:34.848
(COUGHING) Come on. baby.

1013
01:28:34.849 --> 01:28:37.851
(GASPING)

1014
01:28:37.852 --> 01:28:41.730
It's okay. It's okay.

1015
01:28:41.731 --> 01:28:44.191
It's okay.

1016
01:28:44.192 --> 01:28:47.986
We're safe.

1017
01:28:47.987 --> 01:28:50.656
Bryan...

1018
01:28:50.657 --> 01:28:52.116
Kim.

1019
01:28:52.117 --> 01:28:53.117
Kim...

1020
01:28:53.118 --> 01:28:56.578
She's safe.

1021
01:28:56.579 --> 01:28:57.955
She's safe.

1022
01:28:57.956 --> 01:28:58.568
(WEEPING)

1023
01:29:08.091 --> 01:29:13.091
We're all safe.

1024
01:29:35.827 --> 01:29:39.746
<i>Okay-</i>

1025
01:29:39.747 --> 01:29:42.791
Line it up.

1026
01:29:42.792 --> 01:29:46.545
That's it.

1027
01:29:46.546 --> 01:29:48.172
Now. begin to cut.

1028
01:29:48.173 --> 01:29:51.842
Not too fast. not too fast.

1029
01:29:51.843 --> 01:29:56.843
Straighten it out.
Straighten. straighten.

1030
01:29:57.765 --> 01:29:59.016
That's it.

1031
01:29:59.017 --> 01:30:01.351
Stop. stop. StOP-

1032
01:30:01.352 --> 01:30:01.896
Perfect.

1033
01:30:18.369 --> 01:30:20.913
Perfect score.

1034
01:30:20.914 --> 01:30:23.707
Great!

1035
01:30:23.708 --> 01:30:24.917
Congratulations.

1036
01:30:24.918 --> 01:30:29.918
Thank you.

1037
01:30:30.215 --> 01:30:32.925
I was perfect.

1038
01:30:32.926 --> 01:30:35.969
(CHUCKLING) I've been saying that
since the day you were born.

1039
01:30:35.970 --> 01:30:38.180
Congratulations.

1040
01:30:38.181 --> 01:30:41.642
So. what would you like
to do to celebrate?

1041
01:30:41.643 --> 01:30:43.477
Um...

1042
01:30:43.478 --> 01:30:44.561
I think I have an idea.

1043
01:30:44.562 --> 01:30:45.729
Yeah?

1044
01:30:45.730 --> 01:30:47.105
Yeah. I'll drive.

1045
01:30:47.106 --> 01:30:50.067
Of course. (CHUCKLES)

1046
01:30:50.068 --> 01:30:55.068
(CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1047
01:30:58.618 --> 01:31:01.995
<i>Don't knock it till you try it.</i>

1048
01:31:01.996 --> 01:31:04.998
<i>Just come out to LA...</i>

1049
01:31:04.999 --> 01:31:09.999
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

1050
01:31:10.713 --> 01:31:15.092
Here you go.
Three double-chocolate fudge.

1051
01:31:15.093 --> 01:31:16.218
Thank you.

1052
01:31:16.219 --> 01:31:17.761
Who's having the strawberry?

1053
01:31:17.762 --> 01:31:19.555
I'm sorry. but I just
ordered three.

1054
01:31:19.556 --> 01:31:21.932
Actually. the order said four.

1055
01:31:21.933 --> 01:31:23.433
I ordered the fourth one.

1056
01:31:23.434 --> 01:31:25.310
For who?

1057
01:31:25.311 --> 01:31:26.478
(BELL DINGING)

1058
01:31:26.479 --> 01:31:27.938
Oh. Jamie.

1059
01:31:27.939 --> 01:31:30.023
Hey.

1060
01:31:30.024 --> 01:31:31.108
Hi.

1061
01:31:31.109 --> 01:31:32.401
Hi. Perfect timing.

1062
01:31:32.402 --> 01:31:34.361
Jamie.

1063
01:31:34.362 --> 01:31:36.029
It's cool if he joins us. right?

1064
01:31:36.030 --> 01:31:37.489
Of course it is. honey.

1065
01:31:37.490 --> 01:31:40.576
Dad?

1066
01:31:40.577 --> 01:31:42.786
Of course it is. honey. Behave.

1067
01:31:42.787 --> 01:31:45.497
It's nice to see you again. sir.

1068
01:31:45.498 --> 01:31:48.584
(CHUCKLING) Nice to see you. too.
Sit down.

1069
01:31:48.585 --> 01:31:49.751
